###
# API Tests - Coaching Fitness
# Utiliser avec l'extension REST Client de VS Code
# https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client
###

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8000/api
@token = 

###
# 1. INSCRIPTION - PROSPECT
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "first_name": "Jean",
    "last_name": "Dupont",
    "email": "jean.dupont@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!",
    "password_confirmation": "Password123!",
    "role": "prospect"
}

###
# 2. INSCRIPTION - COACH
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "first_name": "Marie",
    "last_name": "Martin",
    "email": "marie.martin@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!",
    "password_confirmation": "Password123!",
    "role": "coach"
}

###
# 3. CONNEXION
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "email": "marie.martin@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!"
}

###
# 4. RÉCUPÉRER UTILISATEUR CONNECTÉ
# Copiez le token de la réponse login ci-dessus dans @token
GET {{baseUrl}}/user
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###
# 5. DÉCONNEXION
POST {{baseUrl}}/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###
# 6. DASHBOARD COACH (Rôle: coach requis)
GET {{baseUrl}}/coach/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###
# 7. ADMIN USERS (Rôle: admin requis)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###
# 8. DASHBOARD GYM (Rôle: gym_manager requis)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gym/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###
# 9. STATISTIQUES (Rôle: coach OU admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/statistics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###
# 10. MOT DE PASSE OUBLIÉ
POST {{baseUrl}}/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "email": "jean.dupont@example.com"
}

###
# 11. RÉINITIALISER MOT DE PASSE
POST {{baseUrl}}/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "token": "token_recu_par_email",
    "email": "jean.dupont@example.com",
    "password": "NouveauPassword123!",
    "password_confirmation": "NouveauPassword123!"
}

###
# 12. TEST ERREUR 401 (sans token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user
Accept: application/json

###
# 13. TEST ERREUR 403 (mauvais rôle)
# Se connecter avec un prospect, puis essayer d'accéder au dashboard coach
GET {{baseUrl}}/coach/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###
# 14. TEST ERREUR 422 (validation)
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "first_name": "Test",
    "email": "invalid-email",
    "password": "short"
}

###
# NOTES:
# - Remplacer {{token}} par votre token après connexion
# - Ou utiliser l'extension REST Client qui capture automatiquement les variables
# - Les erreurs attendues :
#   - 401: Non authentifié (pas de token ou token invalide)
#   - 403: Rôle insuffisant (token valide mais pas le bon rôle)
#   - 422: Erreur de validation (données invalides)
